Dear Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my strong interest in the Business Intelligence and Analytics JMP position at Bosch. The opportunity to contribute to the digitalization of business and product areas while generating actionable insights from complex datasets strongly aligns with my professional skills and career aspirations.

I have completed Master’s in Global Software Development at Hochschule Fulda, where I have gained hands-on experience in Power BI, Microsoft Fabric, Python, SQL, and data modeling. During my working student and internship roles at Bosch eBike Systems and Siemens Healthineers, I developed interactive dashboards, automated ETL pipelines, and performance-optimized data models, improving reporting efficiency and operational decision-making by up to 45\%. These experiences have strengthened my ability to transform large volumes of data into meaningful insights and drive business process improvements.

I am particularly drawn to Bosch’s rotational trainee program, which offers exposure to multiple business units, cross-functional collaboration, and international experience. The program’s focus on entrepreneurial thinking, leadership development, and data-driven innovation resonates strongly with my professional values. I thrive in international, collaborative environments and am motivated by opportunities to inspire others, solve complex problems, and create measurable impact.

With my combination of technical expertise, analytical skills, and international exposure, I am confident in my ability to support Bosch’s specialist departments in delivering statistically sound, model-based analyses and developing innovative micro-solutions using machine learning and modern BI tools. I am enthusiastic about contributing to Bosch’s mission of improving quality of life through meaningful technologies.

Thank you for considering my application. I would welcome the opportunity to further discuss how my skills and experience align with Bosch’s vision and the JMP program.

\vspace{0.5cm}

